          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Johann Lombardi",
          "email": "johann@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-07-05 20:34:23.000000000",
          "tz": 120
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Johann Lombardi",
          "email": "johann@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-07-09 08:39:32.000000000",
          "tz": 120
        },
        "subject": "LU-1604 osd: don't call md_ucred() for OFD",
        "message": "LU-1604 osd: don't call md_ucred() for OFD\n\nThere are several places where md_ucred() is called in osd-ldiskfs.\nHowever, this function is specific to the metadata stack (it ends\nup calling a callback in mdd layer) and should not be called with OFD.\n\nosd_{push,pop}_ctxt() have thus been modified to be no-op when the\nparent is of DT type. __osd_oi_insert() has also been changed to call\nmd_ucred() only when dealing with a MDT device.\n\nThis hack is required to keep compatibility with current MDT stack,\nbut should be removed as soon as the LOD/OSP is landed.\n\nSigned-off-by: Johann Lombardi <johann@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I931f0376a78cb2aff8b00a99b1c20618d4093e7d\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
